      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/28/1/332/6",
      "text": [
        " الله عز وجل: \" وشاهد ومشهود \" قال: الشاهد يوم الجمعة والمشهود يوم عرفة والموعود يوم القيامة."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.basel-kadem": [
          "6.\tWith this chain of narrators, from Hussain bin Sa’eed, from Fadala, from Aban, from Abu’l-Jaroud, from one of the two, peace be upon them both, with regards to the saying of Allah, Exalted and Glorious is He: «And by the witness, and by what is to be witnessed» <a href=\"/books/quran:85#h3\">[85:3]</a>. He said: The witness is Friday, that which is to be witnessed is the Day of Arafah and that which is promised is the Day of Resurrection."
        ]
      }
